<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="37" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="37">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="37">Body piceous. Elytral surface smooth, impunctate, elytral striae complete, 4 setiferous punctures on interval 3, stria 2 absent, prominent humeral tooth at junction of third stria with marginal channel. Profemur glabrous. Abdominal sternum VII with 5+5 setiferous punctures.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="37" type="habitus">
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="37">Habitus.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="18" pageNumber="37">
dorsal aspect, as in 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 49–50" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figures 49 - 50.. 47 Semiardistomis major sp. n. 50 Semiardistomis rugosus (Putzeys). Dorsal aspect. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/19672" pageId="18" pageNumber="37">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
